title: Add ACP (Agent Client Protocol) support for coder subagents
---
Problem
Clawq's coder subagents (delegate, background_task_enqueue, etc.) currently use custom integrations for each runner (codex, claude, kimi, opencode, cursor). There is no standardized protocol for editor/IDE integration with these agents.

Why this matters
ACP (Agent Client Protocol) is an emerging standard from Zed Industries and JetBrains that standardizes communication between code editors/IDEs and coding agents - similar to how LSP standardized language server integration. Supporting ACP would:
- Enable clawq subagents to work with any ACP-compatible editor
- Reduce per-runner integration overhead
- Position clawq in the emerging ACP ecosystem
- Allow remote agent hosting scenarios

Acceptance criteria
- Research ACP spec at https://agentclientprotocol.com/get-started/introduction and document integration requirements
- Implement ACP client capability (clawq acts as ACP client to spawn/control agents)
- Local agent support via JSON-RPC over stdio (newline-delimited, not Content-Length framing)
- Remote agent support via HTTP/WebSocket (optional initially)
- Tool calls, file system access, and terminal operations work via ACP
- At least one existing runner migrated to ACP as proof of concept
- Documentation updated to explain ACP mode
- ACP is an optional boolean flag on existing runners (not a new runner type)
- All 6 runners (Claude, Codex, Kimi, Gemini, Opencode, Cursor) have correct ACP CLI argv generation
- New files: acp_types.ml, acp_transport.ml, acp_client.ml, acp_terminals.ml, acp_history.ml (all in clawq_runtime_core)
- acp_types.ml: Pure protocol types + JSON serde for all ACP types (stop_reason, tool_kind, content_block, tool_call, session_update, etc.)
- acp_transport.ml: Newline-delimited JSON-RPC transport (read_message, write_message, jsonrpc_* helpers)
- acp_client.ml: Core client with connect/create_session/prompt/cancel/disconnect/run_task lifecycle
- acp_client.ml: Read loop dispatches responses, notifications (session/update), and requests from agent
- acp_client.ml: Client-side request handlers for session/request_permission, fs/read_text_file, fs/write_text_file, terminal/*
- acp_client.ml: Auto-approve permissions when auto_approve_permissions=true
- acp_terminals.ml: Terminal management (create, get_output, wait_for_exit, kill, release)
- acp_history.ml: SQLite acp_history table (task_id, seq, direction, msg_type, update_type, role, content_text, raw_json, tool_call_id)
- acp_history.ml: Functions for init_schema, record, get_history, export_jsonl, has_history, format_for_display
- background_task.ml: acp boolean field on task record, DB migration via try_alter, acp column in schema
- background_task.ml: enqueue and delegate_enqueue accept ~acp parameter
- background_task.ml: spawn_task branches on task.acp to use Acp_client.run_task vs Process_group.start_to_file
- background_task.ml: log_excerpt detects ACP tasks and uses Acp_history.format_for_display
- background_task.ml: export-acp subcommand outputs JSONL via Acp_history.export_jsonl
- command_bridge.ml: acp boolean parameter in enqueue and delegate tool schemas
- command_bridge.ml: export-acp subcommand handler
- runner_framework.ml: acp_argv_of_runner returns correct CLI for each runner, runner_supports_acp returns true for all
- docs/src/lib/chat-viewer/normalizer.ts: ACP JSONL format detection and normalization to ChatLog
- Log file format: nicely formatted ASCII text for human reading (timestamps, role headers, tool call details)
- test_acp.ml: Tests for transport, types, history, runner framework, background task integration
- make build succeeds
- make build-minimal succeeds (ACP in core)
- make fmt-check passes
- make test passes (all tests including new ACP tests)
- make ui-check passes (chat viewer normalizer valid)

Notes
- ACP reuses MCP JSON representations where possible
- Default text format is Markdown
- See also: existing MCP support in clawq (P1.M3.E1.T001)
- Related to B129 (/delegate slash command)
- Protocol reference: docs/ACP_PROTOCOL_REFERENCE.md
- Schema reference: docs/research/acp_schema.json
